docker version
docker login
docker run <image_name>	 : Run a container from an image.
docker pull <image_name>	 : Pull an image from Docker Hub.
docker ps	 : List all running containers.
docker ps -a	 : List all containers (including stopped ones).
docker stop <container_id>	 : Stop a running container.
docker rm <container_id>	 : Remove a stopped container.
docker images	 : List all images on the system.
docker rmi <image_id>	 : Remove an image.
docker exec -it <container_id> <command>	 : Run a command inside a running container.
docker build -t <image_name> 	 : Build an image from a Dockerfile in the current directory.




Docker commands to build a web application : 
dir
docker build -t tanmaynginx .
docker images
docker run -d -p 80:80 tanmaynginx:latest  <= if the docker container was not created
docker ps
then paste the ip address in the browser
